  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The publication of \"The Leopard, the Lion, and the Cock\" in 2023 has attracted early interest, evidenced by its commercial accessibility through platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. Its potential policy relevance is suggested by its alignment with at least one Sustainable Development Goal, hinting at broader societal implications.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"The Leopard, the Lion, and the Cock,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2023, is positioned within a nuanced scholarly landscape. While currently lacking citations and mentions across social platforms, its presence on commercial outlets like Amazon and Goodreads underscores its accessibility and potential reach to a broader audience. Such availability is a preliminary indicator of how the work may resonate outside traditional academic circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work also hints at connections to sustainability and policy, as indicated by its alignment with a Sustainable Development Goal. This aspect carries the potential for scholarly discourse to extend beyond academia, suggesting implications for policymakers and practitioners who are actively engaged in related fields.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the metrics indicate a current absence of active public discourse or community engagement, the foundational attributes of the book suggest that it may still contribute to scholarly conversations as it gains traction. The lack of current event data does not negate the potential for significant future impact as awareness of the work grows.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In sum, while \"The Leopard, the Lion, and the Cock\" may not yet have amassed significant traction in terms of citations or online discussions, the framework for its influence is laid through its strategic publication by a reputable press and its connection to relevant global objectives, indicating avenues for future engagement and application. As academic discourse evolves, it will be crucial to monitor how this work is engaged with within both academic and broader societal contexts.</p>",
